		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, "good" old Ninja Gaiden... I remember almost beating my controller to death before completing that game as a kid, and yet the storyline and the cool cinematic scenes made me stay with the game and forgive this abomination of game programming.
<br />
<br />Then about a year ago, I figured I'd play through it again on a dull rainy day... I gave up at level 5, saying there's no reason to put myself through this sadistic crap anymore just to watch an ending scene I could just as well watch on youtube. Oh man did we put up with retarted game logic as kids back then! Guess everything wasn't better back in the old days... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" />
<br />
<br />(and I should again emphasize that Battletoads is my all-time-favorite that I still get a kick out of beating every few years, and I've completed the "Rainbow V challenge" in Viewtiful Joe, so I'm certainly not the one who'd diss a game due to difficulty alone)

		

